additional_fields.field:
Hybridization - The labeled simulated &quot;ChIP DNA&quot; was precipitated with 0.1 volume 5M NaCl and 1 volume isopropanol, and hybridized in 45 ul of buffer containing 20% formamide, 1.2 M betaine, 0.1 ug/ul herring sperm DNA and 10 ug of human COT1 DNA (Invitrogen).  Arrays were hybridized in Maui hybridization stations for 16-18h at 42C, and then washed in 42C 0.2% SDS/0.2x SSC, room temperature 0.2x SSC, and 0.05x SSC. Hybridization buffers and washes were completed using manufacturer's protocols (http://www.nimblegen.com/products/lit/lit.html).
 Labeling - 5 ug DNA was directly labeled by Klenow (New England Biolabs), random priming with Cy3-coupled nonamers per manufacturer's protocol (http://www.nimblegen.com/products/lit/lit.html).
 Nucleic Acid Extraction - Sample received as part of the ENCODE consortium &quot;ENCODE Control 200 ng/ul&quot;
